(42, 18, 13, 42, 23, 48, 48, 'smote upon his breast', 'Expressions of Remorse', 'This connection highlights the act of smiting the breast as a physical expression of sorrow and repentance. Both passages depict individuals responding to their circumstances with a profound sense of guilt and humility.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 14, 42, 14, 11, 11, 'for every one that exalteth himself shall be abased', 'Humility and Exaltation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the principle that those who exalt themselves will be humbled, while those who humble themselves will be exalted. This connection highlights a consistent teaching on humility and pride.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 14, 42, 16, 15, 15, 'exalteth himself shall be abased', 'Self-Justification and Humility', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between self-justification and humility before God. The first passage highlights that those who exalt themselves will be humbled, while the second warns that self-justification is known by God and is viewed negatively.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
