(42, 18, 14, 40, 23, 12, 12, 'for every one that exalteth himself shall be abased; and he that humbleth himself shall be exalted.', 'Humility and Exaltation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the principle that those who exalt themselves will be humbled, while those who humble themselves will be exalted. This thematic parallel highlights a consistent moral teaching found in the teachings of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 14, 20, 29, 23, 23, 'he that humbleth himself shall be exalted', 'Connection of Humility and Pride', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of pride and the virtue of humility. They highlight that pride leads to downfall, while humility results in honor and exaltation.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 14, 19, 138, 6, 6, 'he that humbleth himself shall be exalted', 'Humility and Exaltation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between the humble and the proud. Luke highlights that those who humble themselves will be exalted, while Psalms states that the Lord respects the lowly but knows the proud from afar.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 14, 23, 57, 15, 15, 'he that humbleth himself shall be exalted', 'Humility and Exaltation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of humility. Luke 18:14 speaks of those who humble themselves being exalted, while Isaiah 57:15 highlights God''s presence with the humble and contrite. This connection highlights a consistent biblical theme regarding the value of a humble spirit.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 15, 40, 19, 13, 15, 'that he would touch them', 'Connection of Children and Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the act of bringing children to Jesus, highlighting the disciples'' rebuke and Jesus'' welcoming response. This connection illustrates a consistent theme of valuing children in the context of Jesus'' ministry.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 15, 41, 10, 13, 16, 'that he would touch them', 'Children Brought to Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the act of bringing children to Jesus for his blessing, highlighting the disciples'' initial rebuke of this action. This connection illustrates the importance Jesus places on children and their role in the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 15, 9, 1, 24, 24, NULL, 'Connection of Child Presentation', 'Both passages emphasize the act of bringing a child to a significant place for blessing. In Luke, infants are brought to Jesus for his touch, while in 1 Samuel, a child is brought to the house of the Lord in Shiloh.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 15, 42, 9, 49, 50, NULL, 'Inclusivity in Jesus'' Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of inclusivity in Jesus'' ministry. In both passages, Jesus emphasizes acceptance, whether it is welcoming infants or acknowledging those who cast out demons in His name, regardless of their group affiliation.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 15, 42, 9, 54, 54, 'rebuked them', 'Disciples'' Misunderstanding of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples'' misunderstanding of Jesus'' mission. In Luke 18:15, they rebuke those bringing infants, while in Luke 9:54, they seek to call down fire, showing a lack of compassion and insight into Jesus'' teachings.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 16, 40, 18, 3, 4, 'for of such is the kingdom of God', 'Children and the Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of children in relation to the kingdom of God. They highlight that humility and childlike qualities are essential for entering the kingdom.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 16, 46, 14, 20, 20, 'children', 'Understanding and Childlike Faith', 'This connection highlights the contrast between childlike faith and mature understanding. Both passages emphasize the importance of being childlike in faith while encouraging maturity in understanding.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 16, 46, 7, 14, 14, 'for of such is the kingdom of God', 'Children and Holiness Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of children being regarded as holy in both passages. Luke emphasizes the importance of children in the kingdom of God, while 1 Corinthians speaks to the sanctification of children through believing parents.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 18, 16, 5, 31, 12, 12, 'little children to come unto me', 'Children in God''s Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the inclusion of children in both passages. Luke emphasizes that children are welcomed into the kingdom of God, while Deuteronomy calls for children to gather and learn about the Lord.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
